Update on our re-entry plan:

The Murtaugh School Board met tonight to review our re-entry plan and it was voted that masks will be required in these situations:
On a bus or van, in the hallway at the MS/HS, or when a staff member requests it. This could be so we can work in small groups, help students at their seat or have large groups together that don‚Äôt allow for social distancing.

Please understand we know we can‚Äôt make everyone happy in this situation and are doing our best to take precautions to get back to school. Let‚Äôs work together to make this positive for our kids.

post_text:
MURTAUGH PLEASE JOIN US IN:
Be The Light Campaign #BeTheLightID Murtaugh HS will be participating in the Be The Light campaign that has been a nationwide movement. The idea is to turn on all Idaho stadium lights to show support for the senior class of 2020 and the spring sport athletes, coaches, and families. The lights will be a symbol showing that we are thinking of you all and hope this provides hope and assurance during a time when all school and sports are suspended.

The lights will be turned on Friday, April 10th at 8:20 pm (20:20) for twenty minutes to honor this year's senior class, spring sports and our community support

If you are hoping to witness this event we ask that you drive by the stadium (down Boyd Street) and provide a honk or two. Participants are to remain in their vehicles in order to adhere to social distancing guidelines.

Seniors and spring athletes please park your cars along Boyd Street FACING the road.

Census responses drive decisions on the
annual allocation of more than $675 billion in federal funds to states and communities, which includes support for school programs and services such as these:
‚Ä¢ Special education
‚Ä¢ Free and reduced-price lunch
‚Ä¢ Class size reduction
‚Ä¢ Classroom technology
‚Ä¢ Teacher training
‚Ä¢ After-school programs
‚Ä¢ Head Start

post_text:
This last semester, the 5 students were taking a class on Entrepreneurship and Business. They developed a business idea and were part of a competition through ‚ÄúYou Lead Idaho‚Äù among 6 rural schools a few weeks ago. They won the competition with their business pitch and won $7,500 in scholarships to divide among themselves ($1,500 each) and $2,500 for the school.
‚ÄúYou Lead Idaho‚Äù paid for them to go to Boise on Tuesday to accept their award and pitch their business idea in front of the other groups, the mayor of Boise, and other business owners.

On Wednesday they participated in the High School Idaho Entrepreneur Challenge at BSU. Out of 12 teams in the consumer product division, they placed 1st and won $1,000 cash to divide among themselves ($200 each).

There are more competitions they could enter in the future, and they are wanting to actually start the business.
Their business idea is a web based platform that connects farmers with scrap yards nationwide in order to find cheap parts for farm equipment.

Stop For Our School Buses

Twin Falls Sheriff's Office
December 11, 2019 at 2:27 PM ¬∑

STOP FOR SCHOOL BUSES!!!

Please take a moment to watch the school bus violations that were filmed in Twin Falls County. Each of the videos are from school buses our patrol cars in our County including Murtaugh, Hansen, Kimberly, and Twin Falls. The Sheriff's Office is aggressively enforcing stop arm violations as we work together with our schools to keep children safe from the time they leave home, until the time they return again.

The fine for passing a stopped school bus is $200.00, and is a misdemeanor on your driving record. We would like to thank our partners at each school district in Twin Falls County for helping us with our advertising campaign as well as Town Square Media for airing the PSA on their stations. 98.3 the Snake, 1310 KLIX, 95.7 KEZJ, KOOL 96.5

post_text:
Elementary students will be bringing home raffle tickets today. These are for prizes to be drawn at our Christmas program December 17th. Tickets are $1 each. Please have a name and number on the back of the ticket and return tickets and money to the office. We have some great prizes including a TV, gas grill, gift cards etc.

We will sell tickets for 4 Disneyland park hoppers separately. These are $5 each or 5 tickets for $20. These can be purchased at the office.
